I now have a complete picture of the call chain. Here is my analysis:

---

## Call Chain: `MainViewModel` → Room DAO

The task refers to `@HiltViewModel class HomeViewModel`. In this codebase, that role is filled by **`MainViewModel`** (the navigation destination is named `NavScreen.Home` in `Main.kt` line 78). There is no literal `DisneyRepository` class; the repository is **`MainRepository`**.

### 1. Entry point — `MainViewModel`

**File:** `app/src/main/java/com/skydoves/disneycompose/ui/main/MainViewModel.kt`, lines 26–30

```kotlin
@HiltViewModel
class MainViewModel @Inject constructor(
  mainRepository: MainRepository
) : ViewModel() {
  val posterList: Flow<List<Poster>> =
    mainRepository.loadDisneyPosters(...)
}
```

### 2. Hilt provisioning of `MainRepository`

**File:** `app/src/main/java/com/skydoves/disneycompose/di/RepositoryModule.kt`, lines 28–36

```kotlin
@Module
@InstallIn(ViewModelComponent::class)
object RepositoryModule {
  @Provides @ViewModelScoped
  fun provideMainRepository(
    disneyService: DisneyService,
    posterDao: PosterDao
  ): MainRepository = MainRepository(disneyService, posterDao)
}
```

**Key detail:** `MainRepository` is scoped **`@ViewModelScoped`**, not `@Singleton`. Each `MainViewModel` gets its own `MainRepository` instance. Cross-ViewModel sharing happens only through the **singleton dependencies** injected into `MainRepository`.

### 3. `MainRepository.loadDisneyPosters()` — the cache-then-fetch path

**File:** `app/src/main/java/com/skydoves/disneycompose/ui/main/MainRepository.kt`, lines 32–56

```kotlin
class MainRepository @Inject constructor(
  private val disneyService: DisneyService,
  private val posterDao: PosterDao
) {
  fun loadDisneyPosters(...) = flow {
    val posters: List<Poster> = posterDao.getPosterList()    // Room query
    if (posters.isEmpty()) {
      disneyService.fetchDisneyPosterList()                   // Retrofit call
        .suspendOnSuccess {
          posterDao.insertPosterList(data)                    // Room insert
          emit(data)
        }
        .onFailure { onError(message()) }
    } else {
      emit(posters)
    }
  }.onStart { ... }.onCompletion { ... }.flowOn(Dispatchers.IO)
}
```

### 4. Singleton dependencies (shared across all ViewModels)

| Dependency | Provided in | Scope | File & Line |
|---|---|---|---|
| `OkHttpClient` | `NetworkModule` | `@Singleton` | `di/NetworkModule.kt` lines 35–40 |
| `Retrofit` | `NetworkModule` | `@Singleton` | `di/NetworkModule.kt` lines 51–60 |
| `DisneyService` | `NetworkModule` | `@Singleton` | `di/NetworkModule.kt` lines 62–65 |
| `AppDatabase` | `PersistenceModule` | `@Singleton` | `di/PersistenceModule.kt` lines 31–40 |
| `PosterDao` | `PersistenceModule` | `@Singleton` | `di/PersistenceModule.kt` lines 42–45 |

### 5. The Retrofit service interface

**File:** `app/src/main/java/com/skydoves/disneycompose/network/DisneyService.kt`, lines 26–28

```kotlin
interface DisneyService {
  @GET("DisneyPosters2.json")
  suspend fun fetchDisneyPosterList(): ApiResponse<List<Poster>>
}
```

### 6. The Room DAO

**File:** `app/src/main/java/com/skydoves/disneycompose/persistence/PosterDao.kt`, lines 28–38

```kotlin
@Dao
interface PosterDao {
  @Insert(onConflict = OnConflictStrategy.REPLACE)
  suspend fun insertPosterList(posters: List<Poster>)

  @Query("SELECT * FROM Poster")
  suspend fun getPosterList(): List<Poster>
